{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"82b58860-d57b-49c0-ab69-c3551e816c79","content":"No files found in the workspace. Since there's no existing file to modify, here's exactly how to convert your page and catch errors at build time.\n\n---\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML**\n\nOn the root `ContentPage` element, add the XML namespace for your ViewModel's CLR namespace and set `x:DataType`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\"\n                   VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\"\n                   VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\"\n                     Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"32\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\"\n                   VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is **`x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`** — this tells the XAML compiler the type of `BindingContext`, enabling compiled bindings.\n\n---\n\n**2. Catch binding errors at build time**\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Treat binding failures as build errors instead of runtime warnings -->\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith `x:DataType` set and strict compilation enabled:\n\n- **Typos** like `{Binding Themee}` become **compile-time errors** (CS0117 / XC0045).\n- **Type mismatches** (e.g., binding `FontSize` to a `string`-only property) are caught at build.\n- Bindings are compiled to direct property access — **no runtime reflection**, so they're faster too.\n\n---\n\n**3. Opting out for specific bindings**\n\nIf a particular binding must remain dynamic (e.g., the source isn't the ViewModel), set `x:DataType` to `x:Null` on that element:\n\n```xml\n<Label x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"\n       Text=\"{Binding SomeDynamicProperty}\" />\n```\n\nThis disables compiled binding validation for just that element.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9178acf1-21b1-4c21-8433-84967eb6493d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is asking about a page they have but it's not in the current working directory. Let me check what's in the current directory.","outputTokens":778,"requestId":"D443:101184:1C4D17C:1FD9526:6A07C0AC"},"id":"f8ad6595-9c58-46ac-a31a-6063713bdda9","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:56:27.672Z","parentId":"e7a64054-1f04-4ad2-a452-1f49c016f48f"}
